               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” ["Ḥayq recension"](fols.
                     3ra-82vb)
 - Introduction (fols. 3r-7ra)
 - Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita
                     of Takla Haymanot” ["Ḥayq recension"](fols. 7ra-82vb)
 II) Taʾammǝra Takla
                     Hāymānot “Miracles of ʾabuna Takla Haymanot” – 18 miracles (fols.
                     83ra-95ra)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita has some characteristics of the so-called "Ḥayq
                        recension" of Gadla Takla Hāymānot. Cp. Mss. EMML 1834 (EMML V, 310-14); BN, Éth. 342 (GrébGriaule II, 18-20),
                        Ṭānāsee 162 (SixTana III, 202-06). For a (rough) French translation of the
                        text s. J. DUCHESNE-FOURNET, Mission en Éthiopie, 1<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES901190">901-190</ref>3, vol. 1, Paris 1908,<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES340431">340-431</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The text of the Miracles basically coincides with that of Ms. Éth. 343
                        (GrébGriaule II, 21-25); miracle 17 is absent from Éth. 343; miracle 18 is
                        identical to miracle 17 of Éth. 343.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Decorated quire marks.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
